-- January 19, 2020 --

-- To run --

cd ~/Documents/GRP/data-service
source venv/bin/activate
pip3 freeze
python rest_api.py

-- Details --

1. Install virtual-environment-
sudo pip3 install virtualenv

2. Go inside the project folder
cd ~/Documents/GRP/data-service

3. Create a virtual-environment
virtualenv -p python3 venv(name of the virtual-environment)

4. Activate virtual-environment
source venv(name of the virtual-environment)/bin/activate

to deactivate-
deactivate

5. To check what is installed in virtual-environment
pip3 freeze

6. To install dependencies in virtual-environment
pip install -r src/requirements.txt
(All the dependencies are declared in src/requirements.txt)

7. To run Flask
python src/rest_api.py 

project will run on http://127.0.0.1:5000/

